metadata.name: Death, War, and Collector
metadata.description:
I think it’s obvious to all, Collectors love Art that incorporates a skull, and has an atmosphere of mayhem, chaos, and vicissitude. 
I don’t know why that is, and I don’t think they do too.

This piece depicts that liking of Collectors, that’s why we see ‘Collector’ uncontrollably looking at ‘Death’

I usually do just blue, but I wanted to also draw your eyes to the shadows (P.s: my favorite part is ‘death’ looking back at ‘collector’).

Next time you’re watching a Hollywood movie, notice the night scenes and how the lights: Blue and Orange are widely used.
It’s a color combo that gets the eyes intrigued!
